"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-2024-olympics-a-fascinating-run-fiba-salutes-brave-dtigress-after-usa-defeat\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Federation of International Basketball Association (FIBA) has said Nigeria's D'Tigress superb display at the 2024 Olympic Games will linger on for a long time.  Rena Wakama's side bowed out of the women's basketball event to holders USA, 88-74 on Wednesday night.  D'Tigress defeated world number three Australia and world number five Canada in the group stage.  They made history as the first African team to play in an Olympic quarter-final.  \\\"A fascinating run that we will remember for a long time,\\\" FIBA wrote on X.  \\\"Nigeria, you are leaving Paris on the highest note.\\\"  Transfer: Michael Owen names one signing Man Utd must make before deadline  FIFA lifts transfer ban on Katsina United  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  Why I dropped Cristiano Ronaldo from Portugal squad to play USA, Mexico - Martinez  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"